    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of gram-negative, rod-shaped coccobacillus that can infect humans via the oriental rat flea, causing infection that takes three main forms: pneumonic, septicemic, and bubonic plagues.</Note_Text>
